ANTHRAX, BOVINE - CANADA (04): (MANITOBA, SASKATCHEWAN)
*******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 30 Jul 2009
Source: CFIA [edited]
<http://www.inspection.gc.ca/english/anima/disemala/anthchar/situatione.shtml>


[The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) has updated their anthrax
website to include the Saskatchewan herd in RM (rural municipality)
Canwood confirmed on 27 Jul 2009 and the bison herd in Manitoba, RM
Stuartburn, with bison and a boar affected, confirmed on 24 Jul 2009.

The site is worth visiting, though it has slight outbreak
information, as the maps are very clear. - Mod.MHJ]
